11. Ne4 Nxe4 12. Bxe4 Nf6 13. Bd3 Nd5
{ GM Djukic has played this twice. The idea is to prepare ...Qd8-f6 and make White think about the possibility of capturing on e3. }
14. Bd2 Qf6 15. Qxf6 gxf6
{ I love this pawn structure! Black will continue with ...f6-f5, further cutting down on the influence of White's light-square bishop. Play down the g-file could be on the horizon in some cases. }
16. Be4 f5 17. Bf3 O-O-O
{ = Black was completely fine in Klinova,M  (2302)  -Djukic,N  (2551)  Cappelle-la-Grande FRA 2014. }
