10. Ne4 { This should be met by the usual procedure. } 10... Nxe4 11. Qxe4 Qd5
12. Qxd5 cxd5 13. c3 Be7
{ The engine gives White a half-pawn advantage here, but it's my feeling that the computers - probably influenced by the bishop pair - somewhat overestimate these positions for White. In practice it is never easy to breach Black's ultra-solid structure and weakness-free position. }
