9... e6 10. Be3 { Against IM Arthur Calugar I played } 10... Ne4
{ . That game continued } 11. Nc3 Nxc5 12. Bxc5 Bxc5 13. a4 b4 14. Ne4 Be7
{ keeping d6 under observation } 15. O-O-O Bb7 16. Nd6+ Bxd6 17. Rxd6
{ Calugar,A  (2206)  -Bartholomew,J  (2448)  Dallas 2015. Now the most straightforward path to an edge is }
17... Bxf3 18. gxf3 Ke7 19. Rhd1 a5
{ Black can continue with ...Ra8-a7, ...Rh8-c8, and ...Nb8-c6/d7. White has virtually nothing to attack and stands worse with his inferior pawn structure. }
