{ is clearly critical, damaging Black's structure and refusing to lose time. Now }
6... exf6 7. Bc4 Bb4 8. Qe2+ Qe7 9. O-O-O
{ was seen in the Grandmaster encounter Filippov,A  (2558)  -Golod,V  (2575)  Tashkent 2009. Here I like the look of }
9... Nc6 10. Nd5 Qxe2 11. Nxe2 Bd6 12. Rhe1 O-O
{ Such a middlegame can be compared to the Exchange Ruy Lopez: Black has a slightly compromised pawn structure, but in return he posses a pair of bishops. As long as Black carefully weighs piece exchanges  (you don't want to flagrantly trade down with a worse structure)  he should be fine. }
