{ GM Arkadij Naiditsch  (2700+ at the time)  chose this delayed capture against GM Nikola Djukic at the 2012 World Chess Olympiad in Istanbul, Turkey. It has not been repeated, but given the harmlessness of the alternative, 8. Nf3, I'm giving Naiditsch's move as the main line. Lowinger gives 8. Bxf6 a '?!' mark and deems White's change of heart to be a 'early psychological victory' for Black. I don't think it's so bad, but it also shouldn't refute Black's setup  (of course!)  . }
