{ By analogy with the 'Flank Attack' line, @@StartFEN@@rnbqkb1r/ppp1pppp/5n2/8/3P4/2N5/PPP2PPP/R1BQKB1R w KQkq - 5 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Bc4  a6.   Not  5...Bg4 ??  6.Bxf7+  +- }
6. Ne5
{ This has only been played five times, but it looks like the most dangerous try. }
6... e6 7. d4 Nbd7
{ It's best to challenge the knight on e5 before it gets too comfortable.  Undermining the d4-pawn with   7...c5 !?  was played in Blazkova, P  (2173)  (-Moldovan,C)  (2226)  Brno 2006. However,  8.d5 !  produces tactical complications I think Black is best off avoiding. }
8. Nxd7 Bxd7 { followed by ...Bf8-d6 should not trouble Black. } *

