1. e4 d5 2. exd5 Qxd5 3. Nf3
{ In my opinion this is an underrated line. White does not block his c-pawn as he does with 3. Nc3 and may therefore try for d2-d4, c2-c4, and only then Nb1-c3. The lines I cover in this section are the most forcing in the entire repertoire, so make sure you review them so you aren't caught trying to remember your theory in a sharp position! }
