20. Rac1 { , when } 20... dxc5 21. bxc5 Nd5
{ leads to a position where Black retains the extra pawn but White has undeniable compensation. Obviously Black needs to proceed with some care since it's his king on the chopping block, but the immovable knight on d5 is performing great defensive duty and White's weak c-pawn may slow him down. The engines judge this position to be dead level. }
