{ Believe it or not, you will encounter more than a few players who will decline the proffered d-pawn! Maybe they're suspicious of Black's kind gesture? :- }
2. d4
{ The Blackmar-Diemer Gambit. Taking the pawn is best, but if you're a French Defense or Caro-Kann Defense player you may prefer  2...e6  /  2...c6  , transposing! }
2... dxe4 3. f3
{ As described on ChessPublishing.com, this concept of Blackmar's is refuted by }
